30/03/2010
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Prosecutors filed graft charges against Health Minister Bozhidar Nanev on Tuesday (March 30th). The accusations, the first against a minister since the fall of communism 20 years ago, are related to two vaccine contracts from last December. According to local media, the deals allegedly cost the country 6m euros in losses. (Reuters, Focus, Dnevnik, Dnes.bg - 30/03/10)
